. 2021b: 13
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,1810,2017]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1882,1908]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lobato-Vila, I. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Melika, G. &amp; Guo, R. &amp; Xiaoxue, J. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J." box="[323,618,1882,1909]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref46786" refString="Lobato-Vila, I., Wang, Y., Melika, G., Guo, R., Xiaoxue, J. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J. (2021 b) A taxonomic review of the gall wasp genus Saphonecrus Dalla-Torre &amp; Kieffer and other oak cynipid inquilines (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae) from mainland China, with updated keys to Eastern Palaearctic and Oriental species. Zoological Studies, 60 (10), 1 - 28. https: // doi. org / 10.6620 / ZS. 2021.60 - 10" type="journal article" year="2021">
Lobato-Vila 
<emphasis box="[465,515,1882,1908]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. (2021b)
</bibRefCitation>
claimed the first record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Melika &amp; Schweger" authorityYear="2015" box="[926,1016,1882,1909]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Saphonecrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leleyi">
<emphasis box="[926,1016,1882,1909]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">S. leleyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1085,1156,1882,1908]" name="China" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">China</collectingCountry>
. However, it had already been recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[377,444,1918,1944]" name="China" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">China</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Tang, G. &amp; Shen, J. &amp; Ferrer-Suay, M." box="[486,797,1918,1945]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="17 - 24" refId="ref51876" refString="Pujade-Villar, J., Wang, Y., Tang, G., Shen, J. &amp; Ferrer-Suay, M. (2016 b) Andricus mukaigawae and Andricus kashiwaphilus from China with remarks of morphological differences and inquilines (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae). Butlleti de la Institucio Catalana d'Historia Natural, 80, 17 - 24." type="journal article" year="2016">
Pujade-Villar 
<emphasis box="[642,692,1918,1944]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. (2016b)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,1810,2017]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1954,1980]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Biology.</emphasis>
Reared from undescribed bud galls and galls of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yasumatsu &amp; Masuda" authorityYear="1955" baseAuthorityName="Mukaigawa" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[840,1090,1954,1980]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mukaigawae">
<emphasis box="[840,1090,1954,1980]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Andricus mukaigawae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ǒ, both on 
<taxonomicName box="[1217,1369,1954,1981]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mongolica">
<emphasis box="[1217,1369,1954,1981]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Q. mongolica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[151,245,1991,2017]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,245,1991,2017]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (Table 2; 
<bibRefCitation author="Schweger, S. &amp; Melika, G. &amp; Tang, C. - T. &amp; Yang, M. - M. &amp; Stone, G. N. &amp; Nicholls, J. A. &amp; Sinclair, F. &amp; Hearn, J. &amp; Bozso, M. &amp; Penzes, Z." box="[368,622,1990,2017]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="1 - 84" refId="ref52592" refString="Schweger, S., Melika, G., Tang, C. - T., Yang, M. - M., Stone, G. N., Nicholls, J. A., Sinclair, F., Hearn, J., Bozso, M. &amp; Penzes, Z. (2015 b) New species of cynipid inquilines of the genus Saphonecrus (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Synergini) from the Eastern Palaearctic, with a re-appraisal of known species world-wide. Zootaxa, 4054 (1), 1 - 84. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4054.1.1" type="journal article" year="2015">
Schwéger 
<emphasis box="[486,535,1990,2016]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. 2015b
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Tang, G. &amp; Shen, J. &amp; Ferrer-Suay, M." box="[633,927,1990,2017]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="17 - 24" refId="ref51876" refString="Pujade-Villar, J., Wang, Y., Tang, G., Shen, J. &amp; Ferrer-Suay, M. (2016 b) Andricus mukaigawae and Andricus kashiwaphilus from China with remarks of morphological differences and inquilines (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae). Butlleti de la Institucio Catalana d'Historia Natural, 80, 17 - 24." type="journal article" year="2016">
Pujade-Villar 
<emphasis box="[790,839,1990,2016]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. 2016b
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
